<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>TSI 94-08-03 - Instructions To Service or Upgrade A Suspended Pedal With An Integrated Accelerator Position
        Sensor/Idle Validation Switch.
    </stitle>
    <tsi id="tsi940803" tsitype="truck">
        <tsinumber>94-08-03</tsinumber>
        <tsidate>May, 1994</tsidate>
        <subjectfile>ELECTRICAL</subjectfile>
        <subjectgroup>
            <subject>Instructions To Service or Upgrade A Suspended Pedal With An Integrated Accelerator Position
                Sensor/Idle Validation Switch.
            </subject>
        </subjectgroup>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <lev1>
                    <title>GENERAL</title>
                    <para>This TSI refers to Navistar vehicles with a Cummins CELECT or a Detroit Diesel electronic
                        engine.
                    </para>
                    <para>International trucks built prior to 1994 equipped with Cummins CELECT or Detroit Diesel Series
                        60 engines, had separate accelerator pedal sensors (APS) and idle validation switches (IVS). In
                        1994, Navistar began using an accelerator pedal with an integrated pedal sensor (IPS) that
                        combined the APS and IVS. The following information will allow those customers with pre-1994
                        vehicles equipped with the subject engines to retrofit to the IPS.
                    </para>
                </lev1>
                <lev1>
                    <para>MINIMUM VEHICLE REQUIREMENTS FOR THIS CHANGE</para>
                    <para>
                        <emph type="bold">Detroit Series 60 - All Levels</emph>
                    </para>
                    <para>
                        <emph type="bold">CELECT Software Code</emph>
                    </para>
                    <para>The software code or (SC) number reflects the version level of the software. The original code
                        is shown on the Cummins label on the Electronic Control Module (ECM). If the engine has been
                        updated, the Cummins Compulink APS/IVS, the software number must be greater than those list in
                        <hotlnk xrefid="t9408031">Table 1.</hotlnk>
                    </para>
                    <table id="t9408031" frame="all">
                        <title>CELECT Software Code</title>
                        <tgroup cols="2" colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                            <colspec colwidth="1.28in"/>
                            <colspec colwidth="2.01in"/>
                            <thead>
                                <row>
                                    <entry valign="top" align="center">
                                        <para>Engine</para>
                                    </entry>
                                    <entry valign="top" align="center">
                                        <para>Code Number</para>
                                    </entry>
                                </row>
                            </thead>
                            <tbody>
                                <row>
                                    <entry valign="top" align="center">
                                        <para>L10</para>
                                    </entry>
                                    <entry valign="top" align="center">
                                        <para>SC2711</para>
                                    </entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry valign="top" align="center">
                                        <para>N14</para>
                                    </entry>
                                    <entry valign="top" align="center">
                                        <para>SC1711</para>
                                    </entry>
                                </row>
                            </tbody>
                        </tgroup>
                    </table>
                    <para>If your vehicle has a SC number less than these values, consult your Cummins dealer for an
                        update.
                    </para>
                </lev1>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
