        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="2">
            <title>SERVICE PROCEDURE</title>
            <seqlist>
                <item>
                    <para>Turn the ignition switch OFF.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Disconnect the accelerator pedal harness from the accelerator pedal. Depending on the vehicle
                        Model, it may be necessary to open up part of the instrument panel above the accelerator to gain
                        access to the connectors.
                    </para>
                    <para>25/26/81/82/8300 Models: two 3-way connectors under the instrument panel on the pedal.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Remove the accelerator pedal. All pedals should have two bolts that hold the pedal assembly to
                        the cab. Remove all clamps that secure the harness to the cab.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Place the pedal assembly on a bench or table. Remove both the IVS and the APS. Remove all wire
                        harnesses from the pedal. When this step is completed, you should have a pedal assembly with no
                        electrical sensors or wiring on the pedal.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Install the new integrated APS/IVS. Rotate the APS/IVS until the mounting holes on the sensor
                        and pedal line up. Install the new mounting screws through the APS/IVS into the pedal and
                        tighten.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Connect the 3-way connector on the new pedal harness to the vehicle cab harness (skip this
                        step on vehicles with Detroit Series 60 engines.)
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Cut off the 3-way connector on the vehicle cab harness that was used for the APS. The 3 wires
                        are wire number 99, 99A(5V) and 99-G. Make the cut as close to the old connector as possible.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Strip one-half inch of insulation from each of the 3 wires.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Slip the shrink tube over each of the 3 vehicle harness wires then slide the tube out of the
                        way.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Match the jumper wire to the appropriate vehicle wire and twist the stripped areas (See
                        <hotlnk xrefid="t9408033">Table 3</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Center the shrink tube over the twisted interface and heat until the solder flows.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Mount the pedal back into the vehicle and tighten the two mounting bolts.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Plug the small six-way connector of the new harness into the APS/IVS. The locking clip on the
                        connector should be snapped into place.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>To verify operation of the new pedal assembly, turn the ignition on and monitor the pedal with
                        an electronic service tool such as the Compulink or MPSI Pro-link 9000.
                    </para>
                </item>
            </seqlist>
